<section>
<header>
<p class="scripture-title" data-aid="154411277" id="scripture_title3"><a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/37?lang=eng">Alma&#xA0;37</a></p>
<h3 data-aid="154411280" id="title5">The scriptures have been preserved &#x201C;for a wise purpose.&#x201D;</h3>
</header>
<p data-aid="154411283" id="p6">Consider the miracle and blessing it is to have the scriptures today! As you read <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/37?lang=eng">Alma&#xA0;37</a>, look for the blessings that come from having the scriptures (see, for example, <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/37?lang=eng&amp;id=p7-p10,18-p19,44-p45#p7">verses 7&#x2013;10, 18&#x2013;19, 44&#x2013;45</a>).</p>
<p data-aid="154411286" id="p7">In <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/37?lang=eng&amp;id=p38-p47#p38">Alma 37:38&#x2013;47</a>, Alma compared &#x201C;the word of Christ&#x201D; to the Liahona. As you ponder this comparison, reflect on the ways that you have experienced the miracle and power of Christ&#x2019;s teachings &#x201C;day by day&#x201D; (<a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/37?lang=eng&amp;id=p40#p40">Alma 37:40</a>).</p>
<p data-aid="154411288" id="p8">See also D.&#xA0;Todd Christofferson, &#x201C;<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/general-conference/2010/04/the-blessing-of-scripture?lang=eng">The Blessing of Scripture</a>,&#x201D; <cite>Ensign</cite> or <cite>Liahona</cite>, May 2010, 32&#x2013;35; &#x201C;<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/manual/hymns/as-i-search-the-holy-scriptures?lang=eng">As I Search the Holy Scriptures</a>,&#x201D; <cite>Hymns</cite>, no.&#xA0;277; &#x201C;Alma Testifies to His Son Helaman&#x201D; (video), Gospel Library.</p>
<div class="sc-bvqtyr-0 duiKkI video-vMiKm video"><div class="sc-bvqtyr-1 inwLwu"><div class="sc-bvqtyr-2 hQntbb"><img alt="" class="posterFallback-wNf54" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 320px, 640px" srcset="
